targets.query: SELECT "metric_value" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Host_CPU_Utilization_(%)' AND $timeFilter
SELECT "metric_value" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Session_Limit_%' AND $timeFilter
SELECT "metric_value" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Process_Limit_%' AND $timeFilter

SELECT last("total_space_mb") AS "Allocated Space", last("free_space_mb") AS "Free Space", last("percent_used") AS "Percent Used", last("max_size_mb") AS "Max size Autoextend", last("percent_used_autoext") AS "Percent Used Autoextend" FROM "oracle_tablespaces" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY "tbs_name"
SELECT mean("wait_value") FROM "oracle_wait_class" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "wait_class" fill(null)

SELECT mean("latency") AS "db file sequential read (ms)", mean("count") AS "db file sequential read (nb)" FROM "oracle_wait_event" WHERE "wait_event" = 'db_file_sequential_read' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)

SELECT mean("latency") AS "db file scattered read (ms)", mean("count") AS "db file scatterred read (nb)" FROM "oracle_wait_event" WHERE "wait_event" = 'db_file_scattered_read' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)

SELECT mean("latency") AS "log file parallel write (ms)", mean("count") AS "log file parallel write (nb)" FROM "oracle_wait_event" WHERE "wait_event" = 'log_file_parallel_write' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("latency") AS "log file sync (ms)", mean("count") AS "log file sync (nb)" FROM "oracle_wait_event" WHERE "wait_event" = 'log_file_sync' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Host CPU %" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Host_CPU_Utilization_(%)' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "CPU usage cs/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'CPU_Usage_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Host CPU usage cs/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Host_CPU_Usage_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Background CPU usage cs/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Background_CPU_Usage_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Writes/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Writes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Writes Direct/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Writes_Direct_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Write IO Rq/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Write_IO_Requests_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Writes Direct Lob/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Writes_Direct_Lobs_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value")  / 1024/1024 AS "Physical Writes Total MB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Write_Total_Bytes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value")  / 1024/1024 AS "Physical Writes MB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Write_Bytes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Reads/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Reads_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Reads Direct/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Reads_Direct_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Reads IO Rq/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Read_IO_Requests_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Physical Reads Direct LOB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Reads_Direct_Lobs_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") /1024/1024 AS "Physical Read Total MB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Read_Total_Bytes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") /1024/1024 AS "Physical Read MB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Physical_Read_Bytes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)

SELECT mean("metric_value") /1024/1024 AS "Network MB/s (all clients + dblinks)" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Network_Traffic_Volume_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") /1024/1024 AS "Redo MB/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Redo_Generated_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Redo Writes/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Redo_Writes_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Average Active Sessions" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Average_Active_Sessions' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Session Count" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Session_Count' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Session Limit %" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Session_Limit_%' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
SELECT mean("metric_value") AS "Logons/s" FROM "oracle_sysmetric" WHERE "metric_name" = 'Logons_Per_Sec' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval), "metric_name" fill(null)
